Main Road Network of Alberta All of
Alberta's provincial highways are maintained by Alberta Transportation (AT), a
department of the Government of Alberta, and all of them have been designated by
AT as 'Primary Highways' since 2000/2001. The Primary Highways are divided into
two series, the "1-216 Series" makes up Alberta's core highway network, has the
highest traffic volume, and are mostly paved. The "500-986 Series", formerly
known as the "Secondary Highways", provide more local access, and include a
large number of gravel highways.
